{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make all UK companies pay a fine if their gender pay gaps are not closed by 2024",
        "additional_details": "Companies are too slow at closing the gap. The government created accountability by ensuring companies with over 250 employees reported their gender pay gaps, which had a positive effect. More action by Government can further increase progress for change to ensure equal pay is achieved. Accountability to action is needed.",
        "background": "To create accountability to close the gender pay gap, so that it does not take another 100 years to close the gap. Equal pay, for equal work.",
